WEBVTT

00:02.570 --> 00:03.870
Ohh, yeah!

00:03.872 --> 00:06.539
♪ Powerpuff girls
fighting crime ♪

00:06.541 --> 00:09.175
♪ To save the world
before bedtime ♪

00:09.177 --> 00:11.677
♪ Here's the time to shine
when you're fighting crime ♪

00:11.679 --> 00:13.379
♪ Power it up ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:13.381 --> 00:14.847
♪ We got the power ♪

00:14.849 --> 00:17.049
♪ Breaking through the wall,
gonna do it all ♪

00:17.051 --> 00:19.252
♪ We don't quit ♪
♪ Who's got the power? ♪

00:19.254 --> 00:20.887
♪ We got the power ♪

00:20.889 --> 00:23.423
Oh! Yeah!

00:29.197 --> 00:31.531
Announcer:
Space Towtruck, hurry!

00:31.533 --> 00:33.499
You're never gonna make it!

00:38.706 --> 00:39.872
[ Chuckles ]

00:39.874 --> 00:42.241
You're too late,
Space Towtruck.

00:42.243 --> 00:46.078
You only have time to tow<i> one</i>
of these galactic minivans

00:46.080 --> 00:50.950
before that star
goes supernova!

00:50.952 --> 00:54.887
But which one contains
your beloved space cat?

00:54.889 --> 00:55.922
Meow.

00:55.924 --> 01:00.560
And which one contains
his evil clone?

01:00.562 --> 01:02.328
[ Deep voice ] Meow.

01:04.265 --> 01:06.232
Ooh.

01:06.234 --> 01:08.734
[ Gasps ]
Meter Man is so scary.

01:08.736 --> 01:11.237
Buttercup, can I come
into the pillow fort?

01:11.239 --> 01:13.272
You know the rules
of Fort Buttercup --

01:13.274 --> 01:15.074
"No dorks allowed."

01:15.076 --> 01:17.276
Oh, yeah.

01:17.278 --> 01:18.911
Play the next one,
Bloss.

01:18.913 --> 01:21.147
If we don't find out
what happens to Space Towtruck

01:21.149 --> 01:22.648
before school tomorrow,

01:22.650 --> 01:27.587
you just know Spoiler Cheryl
will spoil the ending for us.

01:27.589 --> 01:29.922
Ooh, Spoiler Cheryl.

01:29.924 --> 01:30.923
Mm-hmm.

01:30.925 --> 01:33.092
All right, girls,
time for bed.

01:33.094 --> 01:36.095
You can all watch your
space-tractor show tomorrow.

01:36.097 --> 01:37.597
Together: Aw.

01:37.599 --> 01:39.832
Blossom Powerpuff,
bedtime negotiator.

01:39.834 --> 01:42.502
Please review this notarized
request to extend our bedtime

01:42.504 --> 01:44.437
so that we may watch
the next episode

01:44.439 --> 01:47.106
of "Space Towtruck."

01:47.108 --> 01:50.476
Hmm, party of the first part,
and then I have to have it...

01:50.478 --> 01:53.446
Well, very interesting data.

01:53.448 --> 01:57.283
Oh, all right.
But just one more episode.

01:57.285 --> 01:59.819
Together: Yay!
[ Laughter ]

01:59.821 --> 02:02.455
Do you, Space Towtruck,
take the Robo-Berta

02:02.457 --> 02:04.457
to be your lawfully
wedded space wife?

02:04.459 --> 02:05.458
Beedy beedy beedy.

02:05.460 --> 02:06.993
[ Door thuds ]

02:06.995 --> 02:08.294
Meow.

02:08.296 --> 02:10.096
Ahh.

02:12.166 --> 02:13.533
Next one, Bloss.
Next one.

02:13.535 --> 02:15.801
Girls, time for bed.

02:15.803 --> 02:18.304
Together: One more.
Come on. Please.

02:18.306 --> 02:20.640
You said that
four episodes ago.

02:20.642 --> 02:22.975
Blossom Powerpuff,
bedtime columnist.

02:22.977 --> 02:25.811
I have on record
you stating you love us

02:25.813 --> 02:28.648
and would do anything
in the world for us.

02:28.650 --> 02:30.483
Well, of course,
but --

02:30.485 --> 02:32.818
Together: Yay!
[ Laughter ]

02:32.820 --> 02:35.488
[ Sighs ]

02:35.490 --> 02:39.158
Space Towtruck,
heed my words --

02:39.160 --> 02:43.162
the words of Signalclese.

02:43.164 --> 02:47.567
It's time to reveal
your deepest, darkest secret.

02:47.569 --> 02:50.169
And that secret is...

02:50.171 --> 02:51.337
[ TV powers down ]

02:51.339 --> 02:53.005
What?
[ Electricity shuts off ]

02:53.007 --> 02:56.709
[ Clanking ]

02:56.711 --> 02:58.578
Bubbles,
what did you do?

02:58.580 --> 02:59.845
Nothing I know of.

02:59.847 --> 03:01.647
Professor:
Girls, get down!

03:03.184 --> 03:04.450
Together: Professor?

03:05.053 --> 03:06.719
[ Grunting ]

03:06.721 --> 03:08.521
[ Grunts, panting ]

03:08.523 --> 03:10.056
What's going on?

03:10.058 --> 03:12.058
Girls, to the lab -- now!

03:12.060 --> 03:13.526
[ Breathing heavily ]

03:13.528 --> 03:15.728
[ Keypad beeping, buzzes ]
Oh.

03:15.730 --> 03:17.530
[ Keypad beeping, buzzes ]
[ Groans ]

03:17.532 --> 03:19.865
[ Keypad beeping, buzzes ]
[ Panting ] Oh!

03:19.867 --> 03:22.134
[ Keypad beeping ]
Got it.

03:23.538 --> 03:26.038
[ Screaming ]

03:26.040 --> 03:27.206
[ Sighs ]

03:27.208 --> 03:30.042
Professor, why did you
beat up those pillows?

03:30.044 --> 03:32.612
Girls, let me explain.

03:35.249 --> 03:37.717
I have been working diligently
on code name --

03:37.719 --> 03:39.118
Project Slumber,

03:39.120 --> 03:42.054
the creation of the world's
most comfortable pillow.

03:42.056 --> 03:44.423
Who says science
doesn't put you to sleep?

03:44.425 --> 03:45.558
Am I right, Bubbs?

03:45.560 --> 03:47.793
[ Giggling ]
I don't get it.

03:47.795 --> 03:50.730
The goal was to build
not just a comfy cushion,

03:50.732 --> 03:53.899
but a pillow capable
of independent thought --

03:53.901 --> 03:55.067
one so smart

03:55.069 --> 03:56.969
that it would predict
what you need

03:56.971 --> 03:59.071
and fluff itself
accordingly.

03:59.073 --> 04:00.072
Ahh, science.

04:00.074 --> 04:02.241
Is there anything
it<i> can't</i> do?

04:02.243 --> 04:04.276
But something
went terribly wrong.

04:04.278 --> 04:07.580
The pillow I made
was<i> too</i> comfortable.

04:07.582 --> 04:10.783
One snuggle,
and you're instantly asleep.

04:10.785 --> 04:12.985
Well, I hate to burst
your bubble, Professor,

04:12.987 --> 04:17.757
but we got a bigger problem,
and her name is Spoiler Cheryl.

04:17.759 --> 04:19.925
Don't you understand?!

04:19.927 --> 04:22.294
Yes! Maybe.

04:22.296 --> 04:23.429
No.

04:23.431 --> 04:24.597
The pillow's escaped.

04:24.599 --> 04:26.265
It's loose in the house.

04:26.267 --> 04:27.299
The house?!

04:27.301 --> 04:28.768
But that's where<i> I</i> live!

04:28.770 --> 04:33.172
The pillow won't rest
until we're all resting.

04:35.143 --> 04:36.609
Oh, no! Quick!

04:36.611 --> 04:37.943
To the panic room!

04:37.945 --> 04:40.112
We don't have
a panic room, Bubbles.

04:40.114 --> 04:42.615
Any room is a panic room
if you panic hard enough.

04:42.617 --> 04:46.619
[ Screaming ]

04:46.621 --> 04:48.487
Girls, it's up to us
to stop the pillow

04:48.489 --> 04:53.459
before it breaks free and puts
all of Townsville to sleep.

04:53.461 --> 04:56.362
Um, you can
put me down now.

04:56.364 --> 04:58.230
[ Keypad beeps ]

05:06.140 --> 05:07.773
Coast is clear.

05:12.346 --> 05:15.815
Hey, Bloss, what do you think
Space Towtruck's secret is?

05:15.817 --> 05:17.883
Now is not the time.

05:19.220 --> 05:21.387
I think he's still
in love with Neutrona.

05:21.389 --> 05:25.691
I think Space Towtruck's
been a ghost the entire time.

05:25.693 --> 05:27.359
Hmm, yeah.

05:27.361 --> 05:28.661
That makes sense.

05:28.663 --> 05:29.662
Totally!

05:29.664 --> 05:30.863
[ Glass shatters ]

05:30.865 --> 05:33.332
[ Gasps ]
I think it's in the kitchen.

05:33.334 --> 05:35.067
On it.

05:38.539 --> 05:40.673
The pillow's right there.

05:40.675 --> 05:42.508
Let's do this, girls.

05:42.510 --> 05:43.676
On three.

05:43.678 --> 05:46.512
One, two, three.

05:46.514 --> 05:47.546
Aah!

05:47.548 --> 05:48.848
-Aah!
-Aah!

05:48.850 --> 05:49.915
Aah!

05:49.917 --> 05:51.016
All: Aah!

05:51.018 --> 05:53.686
Ah...oh.

05:53.688 --> 05:55.354
Where is it,
Professor?

05:55.356 --> 05:57.857
Hmm.
It appears I was wrong.

05:57.859 --> 05:59.191
The pillow's not here.

05:59.193 --> 06:00.926
Oh, well.
Who wants some cheese and --

06:00.928 --> 06:03.229
[ Grunts ]
[ Screaming ]

06:03.231 --> 06:05.064
Together: Professor!

06:05.066 --> 06:07.066
[ Snoring ]

06:07.068 --> 06:10.336
Oh, no! What was he gonna
serve cheese with?

06:11.706 --> 06:13.339
There it goes!

06:16.544 --> 06:19.945
Aw, man.
That pillow is casing us.

06:19.947 --> 06:22.214
Pillow<i> casing</i> us.

06:22.216 --> 06:23.616
Am I right, Bubbs?

06:23.618 --> 06:25.384
I'm scared.

06:25.386 --> 06:26.786
Focus, girls.

06:26.788 --> 06:28.888
We're running out of time
to watch Space Towtruck.

06:28.890 --> 06:32.892
Spoiler Cheryl could text us
the twist ending any minute.

06:32.894 --> 06:35.227
Both: Spoiler Cheryl.

06:35.229 --> 06:36.228
First things first.

06:36.230 --> 06:38.731
Let's get the Professor
to bed.

06:38.733 --> 06:41.734
The Professor!
He's gone!

06:41.736 --> 06:44.069
That pillow monster
must have taken him.

06:44.071 --> 06:46.605
Game over, man.
Game over.

06:46.607 --> 06:48.808
Bubbles, look!

06:52.246 --> 06:53.279
[ Sniffs ]

06:53.281 --> 06:54.747
Goose down.

06:54.749 --> 06:55.981
I must've clipped it.

06:55.983 --> 06:59.785
[ Doorknob rattling ]

06:59.787 --> 07:01.220
Get in position.

07:01.923 --> 07:03.455
All right, ready?

07:03.457 --> 07:04.490
Ready.

07:04.492 --> 07:05.658
Not ready.

07:05.660 --> 07:06.992
Okay.

07:06.994 --> 07:08.661
Mm.

07:10.264 --> 07:11.263
Huh.

07:11.265 --> 07:14.166
[ Breathing shakily,
teeth chattering ]

07:15.269 --> 07:16.368
Now!

07:18.272 --> 07:19.138
[ Yowls ]

07:19.140 --> 07:22.875
-[ Grunting ]
-[ Screaming ]

07:25.279 --> 07:30.249
[ Meowing ]

07:31.619 --> 07:35.154
Bubbles, you have got to stop
keeping cats in the closet.

07:35.156 --> 07:38.624
But you said I had to stop
keeping them in the<i> attic.</i>

07:38.626 --> 07:40.092
[ Static ]

07:45.299 --> 07:47.299
Hmm. Still warm.

07:47.301 --> 07:48.467
It's here.

07:48.469 --> 07:49.835
But where?

07:49.837 --> 07:54.306
Hmm. If I was a pillow,
where would I hide?

07:54.308 --> 07:56.942
[ Pillow hisses ]

08:00.648 --> 08:04.016
It's in there.
Nobody move.

08:04.018 --> 08:04.984
Eep!

08:04.986 --> 08:07.686
[ Sighs ]
I'll get her.

08:07.688 --> 08:12.224
All right, pillow,
get ready to tango.

08:12.226 --> 08:13.325
Hoo-ah!

08:13.327 --> 08:15.961
[ Grunting ]

08:19.500 --> 08:21.000
I got it, dude!

08:21.002 --> 08:22.568
[ Sighs ]
What a relief.

08:22.570 --> 08:25.571
Now we can watch --
-Buttercup, behind you!

08:27.508 --> 08:28.807
[ Grunts ]

08:29.911 --> 08:32.411
Hey!
Get back here!

08:35.082 --> 08:37.249
[ Grunting ]

08:39.253 --> 08:40.753
Hey!

08:40.755 --> 08:42.254
[ Grunting stops ]

08:42.256 --> 08:43.489
Buttercup?

08:46.861 --> 08:48.661
B-B-B-Buttercup?

08:48.896 --> 08:50.896
[ Snores ]

08:50.898 --> 08:52.564
[ Hisses ]

08:52.566 --> 08:53.866
[ Both scream ]

08:53.868 --> 08:57.069
[ Snoring ]

08:57.071 --> 08:58.704
Why don't we
just go to bed?

08:58.706 --> 09:01.907
I don't need to see
the end of Space Towtruck.

09:01.909 --> 09:04.376
Do you<i> want</i> Spoiler Cheryl
to win?

09:04.378 --> 09:07.613
If we're going to bed,
we're doing it on<i> our</i> terms.

09:07.615 --> 09:10.416
This pillow's been a step
ahead of up this whole time.

09:10.418 --> 09:14.386
You see, to beat the pillow,
we must think<i> like</i> the pillow.

09:14.388 --> 09:15.888
I get it.

09:15.890 --> 09:17.890
I don't get it.

09:17.892 --> 09:19.391
Don't worry,
Bubbles.

09:19.393 --> 09:23.629
You lure the pillow in,
and I'll drop the cage.

09:23.631 --> 09:25.397
Now, act tired.

09:25.399 --> 09:29.902
I'm already pretty sleepy,
but, okay.

09:29.904 --> 09:32.571
Sleepy.

09:32.573 --> 09:33.806
Good acting,

09:33.808 --> 09:36.775
and another perfect plan,
Blossom.

09:36.777 --> 09:38.911
[ Hisses ]

09:38.913 --> 09:40.312
[ Roars ]

09:40.314 --> 09:42.081
Clever pillow.

09:42.083 --> 09:43.749
-[ Roars ]
-Aah!

09:43.751 --> 09:45.317
No!

09:45.319 --> 09:49.088
[ Grunting ]

09:49.090 --> 09:51.390
Blossom, what's going on?

09:53.294 --> 09:56.628
[ Snoring ]

09:56.630 --> 09:58.597
Blossom!

09:58.599 --> 10:00.466
[ Snoring continues ]

10:00.468 --> 10:03.502
First the Professor,
then Buttercup,

10:03.504 --> 10:05.938
and now Blossom.

10:05.940 --> 10:09.508
That's it!
It's on.

10:12.847 --> 10:15.981
Pillow,
it's just you and me,

10:15.983 --> 10:19.084
and it's bedtime!

10:20.454 --> 10:22.021
[ Hisses ]

10:24.458 --> 10:26.091
[ Screaming ]

10:28.996 --> 10:32.031
[ Screaming stops ]

10:32.633 --> 10:34.366
[ Yawns ]

10:34.368 --> 10:37.069
[ Snoring ]

10:49.717 --> 10:51.984
[ All snoring ]

10:51.986 --> 10:55.821
And that's why we need
to follow bedtimes.

10:55.823 --> 10:58.991
Isn't that right,
Mr. Fluff-n-Stuff?

10:58.993 --> 11:01.460
[ Chuckles ]
-[ Growls ]

11:04.165 --> 11:05.497
♪ Powerpuff girls
fighting crime ♪

11:05.499 --> 11:08.033
♪ Saving the world
before bedtime ♪

11:08.035 --> 11:10.869
♪ Battling evil toe-to-toe ♪

11:10.871 --> 11:13.906
♪ Saving the day,
a Powerpuff goal ♪
